prompt:
Check if in the given list of doubles, there exist two elements such that their absolute difference is less than epsilon.

```java
public class Solution {
    public static boolean hasCloseElements(double[] numbers, double threshold) {
        // Your code here
    }
}
```

canonical_solution:
import java.util.Arrays;

public class Solution {
    public static boolean hasCloseElements(double[] numbers, double threshold) {
        Arrays.sort(numbers);
        for (int i = 1; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            if (Math.abs(numbers[i] - numbers[i-1]) < threshold) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
}

